Varsity women&rsquo;s volleyball rivals Kenyatta University and St. Paul&rsquo;s University booked a final date of the annual Savlon tournament set for Sunday at the Safaricom Indoor Arena, Kasarani.Former champions KU beat a lukewarm Daystar University in straight sets of 25-16, 25-12 and 25-20 at Nyayo Stadium to romp into the final. In the second semis, St. Paul&rsquo;s University thwarted Strathmore&rsquo;s ambitions by beating them 3-1 (25-22, 15-25, 25-21, 25-19) to stay on course. In the men&rsquo;s university category, St. Paul&rsquo;s beat Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology 3-1 (25-23, 26-28, 25-20, 26-24) to reach final. It was a case of strategy for JKUAT&rsquo; side who intentionally lost their last preliminary match against KU (3-1) to avoid Strathmore Jaguars in the semis. However, It turned out that the lineup (St. Paul&rsquo;s) they thought was easy to handle was a different preposition as they dumped them out of the race. St. Paul&rsquo;s University will hence face the victors in the semis pitting KU and Strathmore in the finals slated for Sunday, October 16. KU and the Jaguar will lock horns of Saturday, October 15 at the University on Nairobi&rsquo;s Chancellor&rsquo;s Square. In the Secondary Schools category, Hospital Hill meet Githiga (boys) while Kwanthanze face Nairobi&rsquo;s Nembu (girls) in the finals. In the girls&rsquo; academies, St. Augustino Primary School, Nandi County play Kasarani Academy.Men&rsquo;s self supporting class, Thika Road VC defeated Huruma in straight sets of 26-24, 25-25-19, 25-19 to reserve a place in finals against Embakasi. The latter beat Bahati 3-1 (17-25, 25-14, 25-23, 25-13) to advance. Kenya Pipeline (junior players) clubbed Huruma 3-0 ( 25-15, 25-18, 25-15) in the semis as Ruaraka clipped Kahawa 3-1 ( 25-20, 25-20, 23-25, 17-25). Embakasi will face Pipeline in the final.